# GitHub API Token for Downloads Page
#
# The downloads page fetches the latest release from the GitHub API.
# Without authentication, you're limited to 60 requests per hour.
# You can set a token to avoid rate limiting on the downloads page.
#
# SECURITY WARNING:
# - This is a Vite env var (`VITE_*`), so any value set here will be
#   bundled into the client and visible to all users (e.g. via DevTools).
# - Do NOT put secrets or tokens with write access here.
#
# Recommended:
# - Prefer unauthenticated requests for local development, or
# - Implement a build-time or server-side fetch that uses a non-VITE
#   environment variable so the token is never exposed to the browser.
#
# If you *must* use a token here:
# - Use the least-privilege, read-only permissions possible.
# - Avoid classic tokens with broad scopes like `public_repo`
#   (it is NOT read-only and grants write access to public repos).
# - Consider a fine-grained PAT limited to public metadata only.
#
# Optional for local development (not required for production builds).
# Leave this empty unless you fully understand the risks.
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here
